\subsection*{Growth hazard functions}
We found that the hazard function that incorporates both growth-dependent and baseline hazard terms (i.e. $(\alpha e^{\beta X_{i}} + \gamma)\delta$), significantly outperformed both the baseline only (i.e.$\gamma \delta$) or growth-dependent only (i.e. $(\alpha e^{\beta X_{i}})\delta$) hazard functions, irrespective of growth rate (Fig. \ref{fig2}A). However, predictive accuracy was higher for stem diameter relative to basal-area growth. Perhaps surprisingly, we detected no significant improvement in predictive accuracy between the baseline only and growth-dependent only hazard functions.

